## Conjecture (CPRR)
- Hypothesis 1: a deterministic timing benchmark catches model
  regressions that intuition misses. Models change between Ollama
  releases; this script makes the change visible.
- Hypothesis 2: native tool_calls invocation rate is the right
  primary metric for picking a tool-calling model — NOT raw t/s,
  NOT total time, NOT param count.
- Hypothesis 3: the >=3B params heuristic was wrong because it
  conflated 'large enough to do tool format reliably' with
  'large enough to think well'. They're orthogonal — qwen3:0.6b
  proves a small model CAN follow the format if trained for it.

