## Refutation / known limits
- 10 trials is small. Not a chi-squared test. Bimodal results
  (10/10 or 0/10) reduced the variance question, but a model
  scoring 5/10 would need more trials to confirm.
- Non-streaming. Sage uses streaming; behavior may differ.
  Streaming variant filed as a follow-up in TIMING-PROTOCOL.org.
- Single host (mini macOS). FreeBSD numbers may differ. The
  forthcoming FreeBSD test agent should run this script and
  produce a parallel measurement table for cross-host comparison.
- The script assumes Ollama at localhost:11434. Cloud Ollama
  endpoints would need OLLAMA_API_KEY handling — not in v1.
- The tool-call test uses ONE prompt and ONE tool definition.
  A model may handle some tool shapes but not others. v2 should
  rotate through 3-5 different tool definitions of varying
  complexity.
- No measurement of the BUILD-TO-PROD gap: a model may score
  10/10 on this benchmark but fail in sage's actual REPL flow
  because of system prompt influence, context length, or
  streaming-path differences. The benchmark is a NECESSARY but
  not SUFFICIENT signal.

